[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "In Test-Driven Development (TDD), the exact sequence of the Red-Green-Refactor cycle is as follows: first, you write a test that fails (Red), then you write just enough code to make the test pass (Green), and finally, you refactor the code to improve its structure without changing its behavior (Refactor).",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "The Red-Green-Refactor cycle is a fundamental practice in TDD where you first write a failing test (Red), then write code to pass the test (Green), and finally refactor the code (Refactor).",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Regarding the number of test iterations recommended before committing code, it is advised to keep the cycle short and commit code frequently, typically after each successful Refactor step, to maintain a clean and working codebase.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "It is recommended to keep the Red-Green-Refactor cycles short and commit code frequently after each cycle to ensure a clean and working codebase.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    }
]

[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The ISO/IEC 25010 quality characteristics replace the older McCall quality factors by providing a hierarchical model with six major attributes contributing to software quality.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "In the early 1990s, the software engineering community attempted to consolidate the many views of quality into one model that could act as a worldwide standard for measuring software quality. The result was ISO 9126, a hierarchical model with six major attributes contributing to quality (International Standardization Organization 1991).",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The ISO 9126 model (which is a predecessor to ISO/IEC 25010) includes the following major quality characteristics: Functionality, Reliability, Usability, Efficiency, Maintainability, and Portability.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Figure 12.3 illustrates the hierarchy, and Table 12.4 defines the major attributes.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "img",
                "content": null,
                "img_id": "img0_se_theory_practice.pdf__chunk_5161_5161_1179"
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "TABLE 12.4 ISO 9126 Quality Characteristics ... Functionality ... Reliability ... Usability ... Efficiency ... Maintainability ... Portability",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "McCall's quality factors include Correctness, Reliability, Efficiency, Integrity, Usability, Maintainability, Testability, Flexibility, Portability, Reusability, and Interoperability.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "img",
                "content": null,
                "img_id": "img0_se_theory_practice.pdf__chunk_188_188_57"
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The mapping between McCall's quality factors and ISO 9126 characteristics is not explicitly detailed in the provided context, but both models share common factors such as Reliability, Efficiency, Usability, Maintainability, and Portability.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "One major difference between the ISO model and those of McCall and Boehm is that the ISO hierarchy is strict: each right-hand characteristic is related only to exactly one left-hand attribute.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "These models, and many others, are helpful in articulating just what it is that we value in the software we build and use.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    }
]

