                "content": "One major difference between the ISO model and those of McCall and Boehm is that the ISO hierarchy is strict: each right-hand characteristic is related only to exactly one left-hand attribute. Moreover, the right-hand characteristics are related to the user view of the software, rather than to an internal, developer view.",
